title: Pretty good...
review:
For a low budget movie $11,000 (estimated), this one is pretty good. The cast all give pretty solid performances and one is enthralled enough to see how it ends.

I really don't know why they have used the Elder Sign (from the Cthulhu Mythos of horror writer H.P. Lovecraft) as the team logo... very odd.

This is not a horror really, but a worthwhile indie sci-fi movie... give it a go.

title: Great independent
review: Fabulous job for an indie film!! If you can get through the first 30 minutes the second half of the film is absolutely stunning!! It really takes a beautiful turn and the lead (Lara Jean Sullivan) does an amazing job all in her own!

title: Not Bad
review: This is not the worst movie yet made. I watched the whole thing. The ending song was good, one can actually understand the words. I would give this a 3. But mid Star Wars movies are a 3 or 4 max. The limits of low budget kind of force limited sets and lots of talking.
